[1] Cholera - Zimbabwe
Date: Thu, 9 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Independent Online [edited]
<http://www.int.iol.co.za/index.php?set_id=1&click_id=68&art_id=qw1139415488696B252>

5 more people have died of cholera in Zimbabwe, bringing the total
number of known deaths from the highly infectious disease to 19,
state-controlled radio reported on Wed, 8 Feb 2006. The new deaths
were recorded near the central mining town of Kwekwe and nearby Gokwe
South district, the report said.
3 of those who died contracted cholera after they washed the body of
a cholera victim, the report said. The first victim had contracted
cholera after attending a funeral, it added.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
