[2] Cholera - Zambia (Petauke)
Date: Thu, 9 Feb 2006
From: Nita Madhav <nmadhav@alum.emory.edu>
Source: Zambia News Agency (ZANA) [edited]
<http://www.zana.gov.zm/news/viewnews.cgi?category=11&id=1139490174>

Cholera has broken out in Petauke District, killing one person.
District Director of Health Kennedy Kabuswe confirmed the outbreak of
the disease during a District Epidemic Preparedness meeting
yesterday, 8 Feb 2006.
Dr Kabuswe said the other 6 people have been admitted with the
disease which broke out last week. He cited the affected areas as
Kakwiya and Misoro in Chief Nyamphande's area, attributing the
outbreak to poor source of water villagers were using. He said that
villagers were drinking from shallow streams, as there was no
borehole in the area. He has since appealed to Petauke residents to
take precautions by boiling water before drinking and to wash their
hands after using pit latrines.
--
Nita Madhav MSPH
Research Analyst
AIR Worldwide
Boston, MA, USA
<nmadhav@alum.emory.edu>
