[5] Dysentery - Russia (Volgograd)
Date: Thu, 9 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Itar-Tass [edited]
<http://www.tass.ru/eng/level2.html?NewsID=3024957&PageNum=0>

A dysentery outbreak has been registered in the Volgograd region, a
spokesperson at the regional Emergency Situations Ministry told
Itar-Tass on Wed, 8 Feb 2006.
The disease has been proven in 15 people. 20 patients suspected of
having acute intestinal infection are staying in hospital. Causes of
the infection outbreak are being investigated.
A group of specialists is heading to the town of Alkseyevskaya of the
Volgograd region for helping [with] the sanitary and epidemiological
situation.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
