[6] Dysentery, correctional school - Russia (Altai)
Date: Tue, 7 Feb 2006
From: Alfonso Rodriguez <ajrm_msds@yahoo.es>
Source: Itar-Tass [edited]
<http://www.itar-tass.com/eng/level2.html?NewsID=3000111&PageNum=0>

The Prosecutor's Office of the Krasnoshchekovsky district of Russia's
Altai Territory has instituted an investigation related to an
intestinal infection outbreak in the Maralikha settlement
correctional school.
An official of the regional department of the Russian Emergency
Situations Ministry told Itar-Tass, "At present 54 children remain
hospitalized, and dysentery was diagnosed in 25 children. There is no
disease among teachers. A set of control measures is in place."
An inspection conducted in the boarding school has found that the
main infection source was one of the canteen workers who had
dysentery. Additionally, sanitary rules were not observed in the
canteen.
Moreover, the boarding school is overcrowded, with twice the number
of children allowed by regulations in its dormitories. The chief
sanitary doctor of the territory made a decision to close the
boarding school.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
